BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Quiche Two-Way
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260331T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260331T193000
UID:ai1ec-147642-94506@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:We encourage you to sign up for classes online. When you regis
 ter online\, you’ll also pay online. While we will accept walk-ins befor
 e class if capacity allows\, registering ahead of time secures your spot a
 nd creates a more seamless class experience.https://www.inthekitchen-bloom
 ington.com/classesSpring has returned and patio brunch season is just arou
 nd the corner. Whether it’s for Easter\, Mother’s day\, girl’s after
 noon\, whatever— a good quiche is the cornerstone of a lovely\, expansiv
 e breakfast. The trick is developing a flaky crust that doesn’t soak up 
 your egg mixture and turn soggy. Quiche lorraine is a famous French prepar
 ation with crispy bacon\, but a veggie-forward blend with greens and herbs
  can be a crowd-pleasing delight. We’ll practice both! Come learn how to
  nail this staple recipe anytime at home.Active participant style class wi
 th Ava. You’ll leave with your own quiche!
LOCATION:In the Kitchen\, 115 N College Ave\, Suite 014\, Bloomington. Use
  the Uptown Plaza alley entrance between JL Waters and Peach Cobbler Facto
 ry.
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/quiche-two-way/?instance_id=94506
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Best of Un/Filmed: Short Documentaries from Russian-Speaking Filmm
 akers w/Q&A
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260331T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260331T210000
UID:ai1ec-147678-94514@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Un/Filmed is an international documentary film development pro
 ject and a regular partner with the Byrnes Institute at IU focused on pres
 erving the tradition of independent\, Russian-language documentary filmmak
 ing\, providing competitive workshops for participants with the opportunit
 y to create films reflecting on pressing social issues. This program is sh
 owcasing the top six films of the 2024-2025 cohort with subtitles presente
 d in English.A Q&A with Un/Filmed organizer and founder Victor Ilyukhin wi
 ll follow the screening.Like Mother\, Like Daughter (dir. Sofia Sedlova\, 
 2025\, Russia and France):We’re Fine (dir. Daria Yurishcheva\, 2025\, Ru
 ssia and France):She Became a Pillar of Salt (dir. Xenia Vasilkova\, 2025\
 , Russia)Uneasy Living (dir. Nikita Nadezhdin\, 2025\, Russia)Kozlov Mitya
 \, 81+ (dir. Yulia Ruzmanova\, 2025\, Russia)Memory is Me? (dir. Vlada Lod
 esk\, 2025\, Russia)
LOCATION:IU Cinema\, 1213 East Seventh St. (on the North side of the IU Au
 ditorium)\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/best-of-un-filmed-short-documentaries-from-russ
 ian-speaking-filmmakers-w-qa/?instance_id=94514
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Daniel Tosh: My First Farewell Tour
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260331T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260331T210000
UID:ai1ec-147753-94535@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:Daniel is widely known for hosting and creating TOSH.0 on Come
 dy Central. The show showcased internet clips with the addition of Daniel
 ’s comedic perspective and was one of the longest-running comedy series 
 for Comedy Central.He can currently be heard and seen hosting his video po
 dcast\, TOSH SHOW. The show premiered garnering millions of watches and li
 stens in the first weeks.Daniel has performed live stand-up comedy to sold
  out venues all over the world including New Zealand\, Australia\, Montrea
 l\, and Ireland. Following his 2025 US Daniel Tosh Live tour\, he just ann
 ounced his new 2026 North America stand-up tour\, Daniel Tosh: My First Fa
 rewell Tour.
LOCATION:IU Auditorium\, 1211 East 7th St.\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/daniel-tosh-my-first-farewell-tour/?instance_id
 =94535
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Death Cafe
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260331T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260331T210000
UID:ai1ec-146809-94116@wfhb.org
DESCRIPTION:A Death Cafe is a group-directed discussion of death with no a
 genda\, ideology\, objectives\, or themes. It is a discussion group rather
  than grief support or counseling session. Death Cafes have spread quickly
  around the world. Over 16\,500 Death Cafes are held in 85 countries. It i
 s all volunteer-run.The monthly Death Cafe at Morgenstern Books is run by 
 co-hosts Rick Clayton and Casey Stover. Rick Clayton is a hospice chaplain
 \, end-of life doula\, and musician who enjoys playing harp\, cello\, and 
 guitar for his clients. Casey Stover is a Certified Family Life Educator w
 hose professional work often exists adjacent to death and grief\, shaping 
 her belief in the importance of accessible spaces to normalize honest conv
 ersation and community care.You can find our Death Cafe at the back corner
  of the bookstore\, near the restrooms\, on the last Tuesday of every mont
 h at 7 pm.
LOCATION:Morgenstern Books & Cafe\, 849 South Auto Mall Road\, Bloomington
URL:https://wfhb.org/event/death-cafe-7/?instance_id=94116
X-SOURCE:WFHB Community Calendar
END:VEVENT
